name: SVGElement
description: All of the SVG DOM interfaces that correspond directly to elements in the SVG language derive from the SVGElement interface.

members.name: SVGElement.dataset
members.description: A DOMStringMap object which provides a list of key/value pairs of named data attributes which correspond to custom data attributes attached to the element. These can also be defined in SVG using attributes of the form data-*, where * is the key name for the pair. This works just like HTML's HTMLElement.dataset property and HTML's data-* global attribute.

members.name: SVGElement.id
members.description: A DOMString representing the value of the id attribute on the given element, or the empty string if id is not present.

members.name: SVGElement.xmlbase
members.description: A DOMString corresponding to the xml:base attribute on the given element.

members.name: SVGElement.ownerSVGElement
members.description: An SVGSVGElement referring to the nearest ancestor <svg> element. null if the given element is the outermost <svg> element.

members.name: SVGElement.viewportElement
members.description: The SVGElement, which established the current viewport. Often, the nearest ancestor <svg> element. null if the given element is the outermost <svg> element.
